### 3.3 Hate Speech Detection  

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[512, 696, 881, 919]]<|/det|>
We selected the two highest and two lowest performing transformer- based hate speech detection models from the zero- shot analysis reported by Cooper et al. (2023) for evaluation on the human- annotated sample \((N = 700)\) of the OTH dataset (the models analyzed are listed in Appendix A, subsection A.4). GPT and Llama direct and indirect normalization and the four existing normalization tools were applied to the real- world homologymfed tweets. Average cosine similarity and Levenshtein distances were calculated, and the four hate speech detection models were evaluated under both a zero- shot and five- fold cross- validation setting for each normalization method.

